latestPosts.caption:
context to the clips:
1. The sweet girl (Nanami 💗) who helped me with directions from the metro station to my hotel. (PS: she went totally out of the way and was ready to walk me right upto the hotel even though she had to go the other way) 🥺🫶🏽<3

2. The cute and cheerful girl who helped me click pictures at Shibuya Crossing (since I was there by myself)💗💗🥹📸

3. The kind girl who spent a couple minutes w me at the metro station figuring why the vending machine wasn’t working (turns out it was actually out of service and we had a little laugh over it 🥹🤭) <3

4. The sweet girl who helped me operate the ticketing machine at the Shinjuku Metro Station (everything was written in Japanese, so I was having trouble figuring it out) 🫶🏽🎟️

5. Vanyaaa! The cool friend I made while sitting at a rooftop restaurant at Shibuya watching the crossing (we spent the next few hours exploring the city together that night, it was the BEST time) 🥹💗⭐️
@diaryofvanya I miss you bbg!!

6. The cute friends I made while dancing at Tokyo Nightclub the same night!!! <3👯‍♀️

7. The kind cashier girl at the rooftop restaurant in Shibuya who I requested for a piece of paper (since I had forgotten my journal in the hotel room) and she proceeded to print a blank receipt so I could write on it and also gave me her own pen🥹💗📝

8. The sweet lady in the metro who gave me the warmest smile as she saw me get all excited and nervous as the train approached Shibuya station and I was getting ready to get off. 🥹💗🎋<3

PS: Beyond grateful for all of these experiences. I shall cherish them forever💗🧿

Also, here’s hoping this video reaches these beautiful women and let’s them know that I still think about them and their kindness! 🥹❤️🫶🏽

Hope to see you again, Japan. ❤️
